aven't left your parents' basement since you got an Apple II in but eventually you're going to need to link up with some human being other than your though I suppose if you're this much of a nerd you could send your mother out to get it for While you're gathering your nerves for a venture into the strange and terrifying world of daylight please don't bother the net by asking this question There simply is no way to move executable Macintosh programs from a PC or other non Macintosh computer onto a Mac without software that is not bundled with most TROUBLESHOOTING WHAT TO DO BEFORE POSTING WHEN THINGS GO WRONG While the various FAQ lists cover a lot of specific problems there are far more problems that aren't covered These are a few basic techniques you should follow before asking for You should probably also perform the ten step preventative maintenance routine described in section four especially rebuilding the desktop and resizing the system heap Following these steps may or may not solve your problem but it will at least make it easier for others to recommend solutions to IDENTIFY THE Microsoft Word is crashing doesn't say What were you doing when it crashed Can you repeat the actions that lead to the crash The more information you provide about the actions preceding the crash the more likely it is someone can help The more precisely you've identified the problem and the actions preceding it Step the easier it will be to tell if the following steps fix the For example Sometimes QuarkXPress crashes with a coprocessor not installed is not nearly as helpful as QuarkXPress crashes when I link two text boxes on a master page when copies of those text boxes already contain The former will leave you wondering whether the bug remains after a given The latter lets you go right to the problem and see if it's still there or READ THE READ ME Many companies include a list of known incompatibilities and bugs in their READ ME Often these aren't documented in the Read any READ ME files to see if any of the problems sound CHECK FOR Run Disinfectant or another anti viral across your Virus infections are rarer than most people think but they do occur and they do cause all sorts of weird problems when they REINSTALL THE APPLICATION AND ALL ITS SUPPORT For half a dozen reasons external magnetic fields improperly written software the alignment of the planets a file on a disk may not contain the data it's supposed to This can cause all types of unexplained unusual Restoring from original masters will normally fix REINSTALL THE SYSTEM Bits are even more likely to get twiddled in the system file than in the application and the effects can be just as See question for a detailed procedure for performing a clean If the problem continues to occur after you've taken these steps chances are you've found either a conflict between your application and some other software or a genuine bug in the So it's time to ISOLATE THE You need to find the minimal system on which the problem will assert Here are the basic steps of isolating the cause of a system or application crash Run only one application at a Occasionally applications do conflict with each If the problem does not manifest itself without other applications running simultaneously you can begin launching other applications until you find the one that causes the If you're running System turn off If you're running System allot as much memory to the application as you can Sometimes programs just need more memory especially when performing complicated If you're running System turn off virtual memory and bit There's still an awful lot of System hostile software out there including some from companies that really have no Can you say Microsoft Word boys and girls I knew you Some of this software only expresses its incompatibilities when certain uncommon actions are Boot from a virgin system If the problem disappears you likely have an init You need to progressively remove extensions until the problem Use a little common sense when choosing the first extensions to If the problem occurs when you try to open a file remove any inits that mess with the Standard File Open procedure such as Super Boomerang If the problem remains after the obvious candidates have been eliminated either remove the remaining extensions one at a time or if you have a lot of them perform a binary search by removing half of the extensions at a Once the problem disappears add half of the most recently removed set Continue until you've narrowed the conflict down to one When you think you've found the offending init restart with only that init enabled just to make sure that it and it alone is indeed causing the CONTACT TECHNICAL By now you should have a very good idea of when where and why the conflict If a tech support number is available for the software call If you're lucky the company will have a work around or fix If not perhaps they'll at least add the bug to their database of problems to be fixed in the next PREVENTIVE MAINTENANCE You wouldn't drive your car miles without giving it a tune A computer is no Regular tune ups avoid a lot of Although there are Mac mechanics who'll be happy to charge you or more for the equivalent of an oil change there's no reason you can't change it The following nine step program should be performed about every three TRASH UNNEEDED FILES Many of the operations that follow will run faster and more smoothly the more free disk space there is to work with so spend a little time cleaning up your hard If you're at all like me you'll find several megabytes worth of preferences files for applications you no longer have archives of software you've dearchived shareware you tried out and didn't like announcements for events that have come and gone and many other files you no longer If you're running System you may also have several more megabytes in your trash can Throw them away and empty the RETHINK YOUR EXTENSIONS Some Macintoshes attract inits like a new suit attracts Seriously consider whether you actually need every extension in your If you don't use the functionality of an extension at least every fifth time you boot up you're probably better off not storing it in your System Folder where it only takes up memory destabilizes your system and slows down every For instance if you only read PC disks once a month there's no need to keep AccessPC loaded all the Cutting back on your extension habit can really help avoid REBUILD THE DESKTOP The Desktop file database holds all the information necessary to associate each file with the application that created It lets the system know what application should be launched when you open a given file and what icons it should display Depending on its size each application has one or more representatives in the desktop As applications and files move on and off your hard disk the Desktop file can be become bloated and Think of it as a Congress for your Every so often it's necessary to throw the bums out and start with a clean Fortunately it's easier to rebuild the desktop than to defeat an One warning rebuilding the desktop will erase all comments you've stored in the Get Info Under System Maurice Volaski's freeware init CommentKeeper will retain those comments across a CommentKeeper also works with System but only if Apple's Desktop Manager extension is also To rebuild the desktop restart your Mac and as your extensions finish loading depress the Command and Option You'll be presented with a dialog box asking if you want to rebuild the desktop and warning you that This could take a few Click It will take more than a few The more files you have the longer it will If you're running System you may want to turn off MultiFinder before trying to rebuild the If you're experiencing definite problems and not just doing preventive maintenance you may want to use Fifth Generation's freeware init Desktop Desktop Reset completely deletes the Desktop file before rebuilding it thus eliminating possibly corrupt data ZAP THE PRAM AND RESET THE CLOCK All Macs from the original Thin Mac to the Quadra contain a small amount of battery powered RAM to hold certain settings that properly move with the CPU rather than with the disk such as which disk to boot Unfortunately this parameter RAM can become corrupted and cause unexplained To reset it under System hold down the Command Option P and R keys while restarting your Under System hold down the Command Option and Shift keys while selecting the Control Panel from the Apple Click Yes when asked if you want to zap the parameter Since you've erased almost all the settings in the General Control Panel you should now reset them to whatever you The one setting that zapping the PRAM does not erase is the date and time but since the internal clock in the Macintosh is notoriously inaccurate you'll probably want to take this opportunity to reset it RESIZE THE SYSTEM HEAP Even after rethinking their extensions as per step two most people still have at least half a row of icons march across the bottom of their screen every time they All these extensions and most applications too need space in a section of memory called the System If the System Heap isn't big enough to comfortably accommodate all the programs that want a piece of it they all start playing King of the Mountain on the system heap knocking each other off to get bigger pieces for themselves and trying to climb back on after they get knocked All this fighting amongst the programs severely degrades system performance and almost inevitably crashes the If you're using System your Macintosh will automatically resize the system heap as necessary but if you're running System it's important to set your system heap size large enough to manage all your extensions and By default this size is set to way too small for most Macs with any extensions at The system heap size is stored in the normally non editable boot blocks of every system Bill Steinberg's freeware utility BootMan not only lets you resize your system heap but even checks how much memory your heap is already using so it can tell how much needs to be If you're running System get BootMan use it and be amazed at how infrequently your Macintosh REINSTALL THE SYSTEM SOFTWARE System files can become corrupt and fragmented especially if you've stored lots of fonts and desk accessories inside Merely updating the System software will often not fix system file I recommend doing a clean Here's how Boot from the installer floppy of your System Copy any non standard fonts and desk accessories out of your System file into a temporary Trash the System file on your hard Also trash the Finder MultiFinder DA Handler and all other standard Apple extensions like Control Panel and These will all be replaced in the new If you're running or installing System move everything in the Extensions Control Panels and Preferences folders into the top level of the System Rename the System Any name other than System Folder is Double click the installer script on your System Then choose Select the appropriate software for your model Mac and You could do an Easy Install instead but that will only add a lot of extensions and code you don't need that waste your memory and disk Once installation is finished move everything from the temporary folder you created in step into the new System If you're asked if you want to replace anything you forgot to take something out in step You'll need to replace things individually until you find the duplicate Reinstall any fonts or DA's you removed in step You should now have a clean defragmented System file that takes up less memory and disk space and a much more stable system DISK UTILITIES Much like system files hard disks have data structures that occasionally become corrupted affecting performance and even causing data Apple includes Disk First Aid a simple utility for detecting and repairing hard disk problems with its System It's also available for anonymous ftp from in the directory dts mac Even if you have an earlier version you should get the latest version from and run it on all your hard Several companies have released payware disk utilities that detect and repair considerably more problems than Disk First Aid though interestingly none of them detect and repair everything that Disk First Aid The three most effective for general work are Central Point's MacTools Deluxe Fifth Generation's Public Utilites and Symantec's Norton Utilities for the Macintosh A department or work group should have all of these as well as Disk First Aid since none of them fix everything the others For individuals MacTools street is about half the price of Norton street or Public Utilities street so features and ease of use being roughly equal I recommend All of these products occasionally encounter problems they can't When that happens it's time to backup and reformat BACKING UP This is one part of preventative maintenance that should be done a LOT more often than every three The simplest back up is to merely copy all the files on your hard disk onto floppies or other removable If you keep your data files separate from your application and support files then it's easy to only back up those folders which change Nonetheless every three months you should do a complete backup of your hard A number of programs are available to make backing up Apple included a very basic full backup application with System With the Performas Apple ships a new Apple Backup utility that can backup the entire disk or just the System folder onto The previously mentioned Norton Utilities for the Mac and MacTools Deluxe include more powerful floppy backup utilities that incorporate compression and incremental Finally if you're lucky enough to have a Tape Drive network server or removable media device to use for backups you should check out the more powerful payware utilities Redux street doesn't support tape drives and Diskfit Pro street There are NO freely available backup utilities other than the old HD Backup from System DISK DEFRAGMENTATION As disks fill up it gets harder and harder to find enough free space in the same place to write large Therefore the operating system will often split larger files into pieces to be stored in different places on your hard As files become more and more fragmented performance can There are several ways to defragment a hard The most tedious but cheapest method is to backup all your files erase the hard disk and you might as well reformat while you're at See question and restore all the A number of payware utilities including Norton Utilities for the Mac and Mac Tools Deluxe can defragment a disk in place without erasing Although the ads for all these products brag about their safety once you've bought the software and opened the shrink wrap they all warn you to back up your disk before defragmenting it in case something does go There are NO freeware or shareware disk defragmenters so please don't annoy the net by asking for REFORMAT YOUR HARD DISK Just as a floppy disk needs to be initialized before use so a hard disk must be formatted before it can hold You don't need to reformat every three months but when your system is crashing no matter what you try reformatting is the ultimate means of wiping the slate Reformatting your hard disk may even gain you a few extra megabytes of Not all hard disks are created Some can hold more data than To facilitate mass production and advertising without a lot of asterisks megabytes is the average formatted Your mileage may Apple often formats drives to the lowest common denominator of drive When you reformat there's no reason at all not to reclaim whatever unused space Apple's left on your Unlike floppies hard disks need a special program to initialize Most hard disks come with formatting Apple's disks and System software ship with HD SC setup a minimal disk formatter which will format Apple brand hard drives Most other manufacturers ship appropriate formatting software with their hard Normally this will be all you need to reformat your hard A number of general purpose formatters are also available which go beyond the bundled software to include features like encryption password protection multiple partitioning faster disk access System compatibility and even Two of the best are the payware and Hard Disk Toolkit Personal Edition street for either While there are one or two freeware formatters available none are likely to be superior to the ones bundled with your hard PowerBook users should be sure to turn off Sleep and processor cycling before reformatting their hard drives no matter what software they Otherwise disk corruption crashes and data losses are a very good Elliotte Rusty Harold Department of Mathematics New Jersey Institute of Technology Newark NJ